        <div id="Chapter 1" class="tabcontent" style="display: none;">
          <h3>Chapter 1</h3>
          <h4>Covered Calls and Options</h4>
          <h5>What is a covered Call?</h5>
          <p>A covered call is a trading strategy where you own a stock and sell options on it. This is an easy way to start trading while also making a decent profit. </p>
          <h4>Let's Break This Down</h4>
          <h5>What is an Option and What Does it Mean to Sell it?</h5>
          <p>An option is a derivative (think Latin roots, not math), which means that it is not the actual stock, but a form of it that moves based on the actual stock (called an underlying).</p>
          <p>Example: 100 shares of Apple stock would cost $15,500, but an option for 100 shares would cost $500. If Apple goes up $5 a share, you make the same profit $500. That is 3% if you own the stock, but 100% if you own the option.</p>
        </div>

